HEADWORD: Zechstein
<hw>Zech"stein`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr., fr.
<ets>zeche</ets> a mine + <ets>stein</ets> a stone.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The upper division of the Permian (Dyas) of
Europe. The prevailing rock is a magnesian limestone.</def>⟦br⟧
